Reusing code
Code is made available for reuse by placing it in a class.


Code is reused in one of several ways
include
class
...


Paramaters to reusable code
Parameterization is handled differently depending on how code is reused.
If reused via include, the parameters are resolved using hiera
If reused via class, the parameters are resolved using both passed in parms and hiera.


Class-based reused is limiting in that a class can only be reused once in a single catalog.
Classes can be included any number of times.



